Escalate privileges to Root - sudo su
Add a new group - groupadd (name)
verify new group - cat /etc/group
Add a new user - adduser (name), add password when prompted and fill other fields if necessary
Add a user to group - usermod -G (groupname) (username)
verify new users in the password file - cat /etc/passwd
view created users in shadow file - cat /etc/shadow
To identify open port - nmap localhost
To use administrative privileges with Nmap - sudo nmap –sU localhost
To perform a version detection to research vulnerability - nmap –sV localhost
To initiate a script scan and capture SSH keys - nmap –A localhost
To open a steghide .odt file - libreoffice <filename> &
To open a steghide image file - gimp <imagefilename> &
To embed a document in steghide - steghide embed -cf <carrierfilename> -ef <embed document>
To verify hidden steghide file - steghide info <carrierfilename>
To extract the hidden steghide file - steghide extract -sf <carrierfilename>
To create a new user - sudo useradd -m <username>
To add password to the user - sudo passwd <username> and follow the prompt
To add user to the sudo group - sudo usermod -a -G sudo username
To change the default shell of the added user from default shell to bash - sudo chsh -s /bin/bash username
Switching users using the su command - su username
To trace the pathway to an external web server on the internet - tracert <ip address>
To observe network failover in command prompt we ping using - ping -t <ip address>
To remotely connect to router - ssh -l admin <default gateway> 